<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1921-10-27T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1921-10-27T17:00:00-05:00" n="297" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d297">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">893.51/3533: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Schurman</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1921-10-27T17:00:00-05:00"><hi rend="italic">October 27,
                                        1921—5 p.m.</hi></date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>288. Your telegram 367, October 22, 4 p.m. By whom was suggestion made
                            that control over proceeds of increased customs duties should be vested
                            in Minister of Finance, Inspector General of Customs and Bankers’
                            Association?</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hughes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
